9
00:00:22,039 --> 00:00:24,800
the former bishop of the Catholic Church in
Hong Kong.

10
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:27,499
He's been an outspoken defender of human rights
and has been called

11
00:00:27,499 --> 00:00:29,590
the conscience of Hong Kong.

12
00:00:29,590 --> 00:00:30,699
Thank you for joining me today.

13
00:00:30,699 --> 00:00:31,699
Thank you.

14
00:00:31,699 --> 00:00:34,039
So, for those watching, could you give us
an idea of

15
00:00:34,039 --> 00:00:37,809
what it's like to be a Christian in China?

16
00:00:37,809 --> 00:00:44,390
It's very complicated thing because in the
constitution

17
00:00:44,390 --> 00:00:47,899
they say there is freedom for religion,

18
00:00:47,899 --> 00:00:54,830
but actually you have to follow the directive
of the government.

19
00:00:54,830 --> 00:01:04,949
Recently, it seems that they are particularly
worried about

20
00:01:04,949 --> 00:01:07,490
the so-called foreign religion,

21
00:01:07,490 --> 00:01:09,630
especially the Christian religion.

22
00:01:09,630 --> 00:01:13,830
So, they have hard life.

23
00:01:13,830 --> 00:01:15,280
We Catholics in China,

24
00:01:15,280 --> 00:01:21,840
we have a big problem because we are split
into two communities.

25
00:01:21,840 --> 00:01:25,090
One, the so-called underground,

26
00:01:25,090 --> 00:01:30,110
those who want to keep their faith and refuse

27
00:01:30,110 --> 00:01:33,590
to follow the directive of the party

28
00:01:33,590 --> 00:01:38,240
because religion is not part of the party.

29
00:01:38,240 --> 00:01:41,340
There is another part, another community,

30
00:01:41,340 --> 00:01:48,189
for any reason they thought it's okay to accommodate
and compromise,

31
00:01:48,189 --> 00:01:50,570
and they follow the government.

32
00:01:50,570 --> 00:01:55,180
Being separated into two community create
other problems.

33
00:01:55,180 --> 00:01:58,040
So, there's basically the state-run churches

34
00:01:58,040 --> 00:02:00,780
controlled by the Chinese Communist Party

35
00:02:00,780 --> 00:02:03,789
and those who worship underground, as you
say.

36
00:02:03,789 --> 00:02:04,789
Yeah.

37
00:02:04,789 --> 00:02:07,719
What kind of pressure do the underground Christians
face?

38
00:02:07,719 --> 00:02:12,069
You see, China is so big so the situation

39
00:02:12,069 --> 00:02:16,370
is different from place to place.

40
00:02:16,370 --> 00:02:22,790
You can have a place where the underground
is the majority

41
00:02:22,790 --> 00:02:25,620
or other places where they are the minority.

42
00:02:25,620 --> 00:02:33,980
You may have a place where they can live in
a peaceful coexistence.

43
00:02:33,980 --> 00:02:38,450
Then you have other places where they fight
each other.

44
00:02:38,450 --> 00:02:42,739
It's a very different situation.

45
00:02:42,739 --> 00:02:49,409
Now, I make some important example, for example,
in Shanghai.

46
00:02:49,409 --> 00:02:52,790
Shanghai is my native city.

47
00:02:52,790 --> 00:02:56,780
In Shanghai you have both communities rather
strong.

48
00:02:56,780 --> 00:03:02,319
Then, they live almost peacefully together.

49
00:03:02,319 --> 00:03:08,430
Then in other places,

50
00:03:08,430 --> 00:03:14,060
